==English==
===Etymology===
From [[betime]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/bɪˈtaɪmz/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪmz|-aɪmz]]

===Adverb===
'''betimes'''
# In good season or time; [[early]], especially early in the morning
# In a short time, [[soon]]

====Quotations====
*I was up betimes in the morning, but Holmes was afoot earlier still, for I saw him as I dressed, coming up the drive. — Arthur Conan Doyle, ''The Hound of the Baskervilles''

